=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Trig_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 800 Hz, featuring very_slow attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, energy distribution is late, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: very_slow
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: very_dynamic
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: late

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 800.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: -4.2053
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5496
  pitch_clarity: 79.6647
  inharmonicity: 0.0050
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -2.5644
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Trig Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Trig.html
// Tags: Trig, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ Trig.ar(Dust.ar(1), 0.2) * FSinOsc.ar(800, 0.5) }.play

{ Trig.ar(Dust.ar(4), 0.1) }.play
